    "name": "Stables-HT-HOL-ONLY-3RD-SOURCE-time-daily-2",
    "description": "HOLDER Portfolio: Track USD ↔ USDC conversions based on PUBLISHED risk metrics\n════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSIMPLIFIED APPROACH:\n  - Portfolio tracking ONLY: Your USD and USDC balances\n  - Risk metrics are EXTERNAL INDICES (read from 3rd party sources)\n  - NO complex behavioral models or calculations\n  - Simple decision: Good metrics → buy USDC | Bad metrics → sell to USD\n\nRISK METRICS (as Reference Indices):\n  1. Backing Ratio (BR): Published reserve coverage (0.0=100%+ backed, 1.0=underbacked)\n  2. Liquidity Score (LQ): Published liquidity adequacy (0.0=adequate, 1.0=crisis)\n  3. Peg Stability (PEG): Price deviation from $1.00 (0.0=stable, 0.05=5% off-peg)\n  4. Market Risk (MR): Composite market stress (0.0=calm, 1.0=panic)\n\nPORTFOLIO:\n  - Start: $150,000 USD, $0 USDC\n  - Target: $75,000 USDC when metrics are good\n  - Crisis: Convert all USDC → USD when metrics deteriorate\n  - Recovery: Rebuild USDC position when metrics improve\n\nSCENARIO (45 days):\n  Days 1-3:   Good metrics → Deploy to $75K USDC\n  Days 4-17:  Good metrics → Hold $75K USDC\n  Day 18:     Metrics spike → Redeem all USDC to USD\n  Days 19-25: Bad metrics → Stay in USD\n  Days 26-28: Metrics recover → Rebuild to $75K USDC\n  Days 29-45: Good metrics → Hold $75K USDC",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
